STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Daniel Ryburn DUNN, Appellant. No. ED 105400 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION FOUR. Filed: June 26, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied September 10, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied December 4, 2018 N. Scott Rosenblum, Jessica Hathaway, 120 South Central Avenue, Suite 130, St. Louis, MO 63105, for appellant. Chris Koster, Atty. Gen., Daniel N. McPherson, Asst. Atty. Gen., P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO 65102, for respondent. Before Colleen Dolan, P.J., Mary K. Hoff, J., and Lawrence E. Mooney, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Daniel Ryburn Dunn appeals the judgment entered on a jury verdict finding him guilty of first-degree murder, in violation of Section 565.020 RSMo., and armed criminal action, in violation of Section 571.015 RSMo. No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have furnished the parties with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for our order. We affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
